Caitlin Whiteman

My meme

My meme is new and original as it relates to me as a uni student having to work Thursday and Friday and having those Friday night due dates can be very stressful. This meme is the relief I feel when I realise I have the weekend to do it. This meme is fun and original and highlights that funny dog pictures can make any situation more exciting. Also, by using different colours for the block behind the writing it stands out against other memes.

enjoy my meme!

library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

#creating two blank box's with writing
#blank box 1 - the start of the meme - with the first writing portion in the center 
blank1 <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                      height = 300,
                      color = "#d6d632") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "when you think your\nproject is due friday",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 30,
                 gravity = "center")

#blank box 2 - second bit of meme - keep the same size box, different writing and colour
blank2 <- image_annotate(image_blank(width = 300, height = 300, color = "#b3ffff"), text = "when you realise\nits due sunday", color = "#000000", size = 30, gravity = "center")

#meme part 1 - the first image - keep same size box as previous blank boxes
dog1 <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/991047198/photo/smart-intelligent-pug-puppy-dog-with-reading-glasses-sitting-down-between-piles-of-books.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=O0x93EdEfs-r93hiwOU2VnhBtXqiQ5brgPjYcyWB3e8=") %>%
  image_scale("x300") %>%
  image_crop("300x300", 
             gravity = "center")

#meme part 2 - the second image - keep same size box as previous blank boxes
dog2 <- image_read("https://media.istockphoto.com/id/1143749724/photo/happy-dog-wearing-sunglasses-drinking-fruit-smoothie-through-cocktail-straw.jpg?s=612x612&w=0&k=20&c=xDaRAU5rpeR59gzi-L2rnpF-Mn-De4ejI49gyYIISHM=") %>%
  image_scale("x300") %>%
  image_crop("300x300", 
             gravity = "center")

#building the meme - creating 2 vectors, one for the top line of the meme, one for the bottom
top <- image_append(c(blank1 , dog1 ))
bottom <- image_append(c(blank2, dog2))

#putting it all together - stacking the two vectors on top of each other
memeyay <- c(top, bottom) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

#showing meme in viewer to check it is correct
print(memeyay)

#making the meme into an image
image_write(memeyay, "stats220meme.png")

My animated gif

This gif was made as I have been dating my boyfriend almost 2 years and this is what I feel like when I’m with him, like two orangutans in a tree. It is new and original as i have changed the colours and the pictures to remind people of love and happiness.

enjoy my gif!

library(magick)

#build the 4 first blank image frames - each with a different word on it, centering the writing - build in order of animation - frames 1 to 4
frame1 <- image_blank(width = 600, height = 600, color = "#fdcbfa") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "me", 
                         color = "#000000", 
                         size = 100,
                         gravity = "center")


frame2 <- image_blank(width = 600, 
                      height = 600, 
                      color = "#fdcbfa") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "+", 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 size = 100, 
                 gravity = "center")


frame3 <- image_blank(width = 600,
                      height = 600,
                      color = "#fdcbfa") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "you",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 100,
                 gravity = "center")


frame4 <- image_blank(width = 600, 
                      height = 600, 
                      color = "#fdcbfa") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "=", 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 size = 100,
                 gravity = "center")

#build the last image frame using an online image - keeping all the squares the same size
frame5 <- image_read("https://bestlifeonline.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/monkeys-in-love.jpg?quality=82&strip=1&resize=640%2C360") %>%
  image_scale("x600") %>%
  image_crop("600x600", gravity = "center")

#make the frames into a named object vector
allframes <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5)

#animate to make a gif - displayed in the sequence given in the vector made - add a red border
animation <- image_morph(allframes) %>%
  image_animate(fps = 5) %>%
  image_border("#e0282b" , "10x10")

#display the animation in viewer to ensure the code is correct
print(animation)

#convert the animation into a gif
image_write(animation, "stats220animation.gif")
